<Window x:Class="FinancialMarkets.GovernmentRegulations"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        xmlns:local="clr-namespace:FinancialMarkets"
        mc:Ignorable="d"
        Title="GovernmentRegulations" Height="482" Width="1210" MaxWidth="1210" MaxHeight="482" MinWidth="1210" MinHeight="482">
    <Window.Background>
        <LinearGradientBrush EndPoint="0.5,1" StartPoint="0.5,0">
            <GradientStop Color="Black" Offset="0"/>
            <GradientStop Color="{DynamicResource {x:Static SystemColors.ActiveCaptionColorKey}}" Offset="1"/>
        </LinearGradientBrush>
    </Window.Background>
    <Grid>
        <Grid.RowDefinitions>
            <RowDefinition Height="137*"/>
            <RowDefinition/>
            <RowDefinition Height="87*"/>
            <RowDefinition Height="61*"/>
        </Grid.RowDefinitions>
        <RichTextBox HorizontalAlignment="Left" Height="427" Margin="8,13,0,0" VerticalAlignment="Top" Width="581" TextChanged="RichTextBox_TextChanged" Grid.RowSpan="4">
            <FlowDocument>
                <Paragraph BorderBrush="Black" BorderThickness="0,0,0,1" FontFamily="Times New Roman" Margin="0,26.67,0,13.33" Padding="1.33" TextAlignment="Center">
                    <Run FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Segoe UI" Text="Government regulations and policies"/>
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph FontFamily="Times New Roman" Margin="0,0,0,13.33" TextAlignment="Left">
                    <Span>
                        <Run Text="Substantial overhead is required to adhere to the Federal Reserve government policies, this would be the second major competitive advantage. Standard regulations include the Dodd-Frank designing restrictions on the custody bank services with the goal of reducing the total systemic risk developed through individual financial transactions. New regulations implemented in"/>
                    </Span>
                    <Run Text=" "/>
                    <Run Text=" "/>
                    <Run Text=" "/>
                    <Run Text=" "/>
                    <Run Text=" "/>
                    <Run Text=" "/>
                    <Run Text=" "/>
                    <Span>
                        <Run Text="'"/>
                    </Span>
                    <Run Text=" "/>
                    <Run Text=" "/>
                    <Run Text=" "/>
                    <Run Text=" "/>
                    <Run Text=" "/>
                    <Run Text=" "/>
                    <Run Text=" "/>
                    <Span>
                        <Run Text="14 include restrictions on the major capital financial ratios and capital requirements especially liquidity.  New disclosure requirements are required to the federal reserve in terms of planned actions over a nine quarter planning period in terms of raising capital, issuing or purchasing stock and issuing dividends.  State Street parent company is registered as a financial holding company with the Federal Reserve per the Bank Holding Company Act and hence is subject to the rules and regulations of a financial holding parent company. "/>
                    </Span>
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph FontSize="16" FontFamily="Times New Roman" Margin="0,0,0,8" TextAlignment="Left">
                    <Run FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="12" Text="Dodd Frank Act" TextDecorations="Underline"/>
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph FontSize="16" FontFamily="Times New Roman" Margin="0,0,0,8" TextAlignment="Left">
                    <Run FontSize="12" Text="Monitor the level of systemic risk contributed through individual organizations                                                             Manage the regulation of derivative transactions                                                                                                    Regulate capital planning and stress test requirements"/>
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph FontSize="16" FontFamily="Times New Roman" Margin="0,0,0,8" TextAlignment="Left">
                    <Run FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="12" Text="Regulatory capital adequacy and liquidity standards" TextDecorations="Underline"/>
                </Paragraph>
                <List MarkerStyle="Box" MarkerOffset="1">
                    <ListItem>
                        <Paragraph FontSize="16" FontFamily="Times New Roman" TextAlignment="Left">
                            <Run FontSize="12" Text="  Regulate risk items to a company's capital structure including leverage ratios  "/>
                        </Paragraph>
                    </ListItem>
                    <ListItem>
                        <Paragraph FontSize="16" FontFamily="Times New Roman" TextAlignment="Left">
                            <Run FontSize="12" Text="  Regulating the financial strength of the bank in terms of common stock to risk weighted assets "/>
                        </Paragraph>
                    </ListItem>
                    <ListItem>
                        <Paragraph FontSize="16" FontFamily="Times New Roman" TextAlignment="Justify">
                            <Run FontSize="12" Text="  Introduced a new regulation to the common equity tier 1 risk capital ratio of 4.5%"/>
                        </Paragraph>
                    </ListItem>
                    <ListItem>
                        <Paragraph FontSize="16" FontFamily="Times New Roman" TextAlignment="Justify">
                            <Run FontSize="12" Text="  Increased the minimum tier 1 risk capital ratio from 4 to 6 %"/>
                        </Paragraph>
                    </ListItem>
                    <ListItem>
                        <Paragraph FontSize="16" FontFamily="Times New Roman" TextAlignment="Justify">
                            <Run FontSize="12" Text="  In essence, the regulation is reducing the risk of low liquidity and the risk of not meeting capital requirements    in order to achieve optimum operational efficiencies. "/>
                        </Paragraph>
                    </ListItem>
                    <ListItem>
                        <Paragraph FontSize="16" FontFamily="Times New Roman" TextAlignment="Justify">
                            <Run FontSize="12" Text=" Latest modifications to the Dodd Frank Act requires more stringent capital requirements."/>
                        </Paragraph>
                    </ListItem>
                </List>
                <Paragraph FontSize="16" FontFamily="Times New Roman" TextAlignment="Justify">
                    <Run FontSize="12" Text="Additional regulations revolve around limitations on leverage, debt, liquidity coverage ratio focused on maintaining certain levels of liquidity. Capital planning and stress test requirements have been implemented.                                                                  Additional regulations on reducing the risk of derivatives have been implemented"/>
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph FontFamily="Times New Roman" Margin="0,0,0,13.33" TextAlignment="Left">
                    <Span>
                        <Run/>
                    </Span>
                </Paragraph>
            </FlowDocument>
        </RichTextBox>
        <RichTextBox HorizontalAlignment="Left" Height="420" Margin="598,15,0,0" VerticalAlignment="Top" Width="594" Grid.RowSpan="4" TextChanged="RichTextBox_TextChanged_1">
            <FlowDocument>
                <Paragraph>
                    <Run FontWeight="Bold" Text="                                                           Risk management in the financial sector"/>
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph>
                    <Run FontSize="13" FontFamily="Times New Roman" Text="The ability to predict and manage global macroeconomic indicators and hence maintain financial stability is considered a key competitive advantage for financial institutions. Managing risk on fluctuations on interest rates, dollar appreciation values, changes in the money supply, operational risks, new federal reserve policies, changes in liquidity of international and national securities market, credit ratings on the fair value of securities held within portfolios, regulatory changes and data security are essential in projecting forward looking financial statements and making decisions in terms of future investments. "/>
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph FontSize="16" FontFamily="Times New Roman" Margin="0,0,0,13.33" TextAlignment="Justify">
                    <Run FontSize="13" Text="The ability to anticipate changes in the economic factors that impact interest rates is essential to maintaining stable cash flows. The ability to collect accurate global information, make decisions and execute risk mitigation strategies including interest rate swaps and various hedging strategies on the portfolio securities is essential to providing high levels of net interest revenue and hence net income. Business development capabilities in the changing financial environment include strategizing products with competitive value propositions to increase investment. Experience in successful business development includes excellent risk management in terms of project investment analysis, infrastructure upgrades, merger and acquisition business propositions. Fair credit valuations of securities within investment portfolios are major factors impacting portfolio market valuations. Credit rating devaluations, interest rate fluctuations, European market changes in terms of European monetary policy require substantial active research and effective liquidity management by financial managers. The software databases, intellectual property patents on algorithms, models, credit risk calculators, auditing, assumptions, custom applications and platforms depend on data collection and data inputs These parameters are exposed to various risk factors hence risk management is a critical component of maintaining financial stability."/>
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph FontSize="16" FontFamily="Times New Roman" Margin="0,0,0,13.33" TextAlignment="Justify">
                    <Run FontSize="13" Text="Hence customer perceptions on the value propositions that a financial institute provides in terms of risk management generates brand recognition and impacts revenue margins for that financial institution. "/>
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph FontSize="16" FontFamily="Times New Roman" Margin="0,0,0,13.33" TextAlignment="Justify">
                    <Run FontSize="13"/>
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph>
                    <Run FontSize="16" FontFamily="Times New Roman"/>
                </Paragraph>
            </FlowDocument>
        </RichTextBox>

    </Grid>
</Window>
